.TH "platform_get_irq_byname_optional" 9 "platform_get_irq_byname_optional" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
platform_get_irq_byname_optional \- get an optional IRQ for a device by name
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" platform_get_irq_byname_optional
.BI "(struct platform_device *dev "  ","
.BI "const char *name "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
platform device
.IP "name" 12
IRQ name
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Get an optional IRQ by name like \fBplatform_get_irq_byname\fP. Except that it
does not print an error message if an IRQ can not be obtained.
.SH "RETURN"
non-zero IRQ number on success, negative error number on failure.
